  "prompt": "I have heard Reliance JIO locks a mobile phone and the same cannot be used for any other network. Is it true?",
  "response": "No, it is not true that Reliance Jio locks mobile phones in such a way that they cannot be used with other networks. Reliance Jio, like other telecom operators, provides SIM cards and services that are compatible with unlocked mobile devices. \n\nWhen you purchase a mobile phone from any telecom operator or retailer, it may come locked to that specific carrier if it is a subsidized or contract-based device. However, in India, most phones sold in the market are unlocked and can be used with any network provider's SIM card, including Reliance Jio.\n\nIf you encounter a situation where a phone is locked to a specific network, you can typically request the carrier to unlock it, especially if you have fulfilled the terms of your contract or paid off the device. In India, major telecom operators, including Reliance Jio, do not generally sell locked phones to consumers.\n\nFor more clarity or if you face any issues, you can contact Reliance Jio customer support for assistance.",
